USE OF YOUR PASSWORD   OR ACCOUNT COULD CAUSE YOU TO INCUR LIABILITY TO BOTH VACATIONPARTIES.COM AND   OTHER USERS.</p>\r\n<p>When you book a reservation facilitated by the Booking Systems, we will   collect your payment information and, if a third-party offering, transmit it to the supplier to   complete the transaction, as described in our <a rel="nofollow" href="privacy.html">Privacy Policy</a>. Please note that VacationParties.com or a third party supplier may processes your payment and fulfill your reservation. </p>\r\n<p>VacationParties.com and its affiliates will not interfere with reservations   arbitrarily, but we reserve the right to cancel or not process a   reservation because of certain extenuating circumstances, such as when a   reservation is no longer available or when we have reasonable cause to   suspect that a reservation request may be fraudulent. VacationParties.com also   reserves the right to take steps to verify your identity to process your   reservation.</p>\r\n<p>In the unlikely event that a reservation is available when you place   an order but becomes unavailable prior to check-in, your sole remedy   will be to  make alternative arrangements or to   cancel your reservation.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Third-Party Suppliers.</strong> VacationParties.com is  a travel agency service and   only  provides, but does not own,  transportation services or accommodations.   Although VacationParties.com displays information about properties owned by   third-party suppliers and facilitates reservations with certain   suppliers on affiliate sites, such actions do not in   any way imply, suggest, or constitute VacationParties.com&rsquo;s sponsorship or   approval of third-party suppliers, or any affiliation between   VacationParties.com and third-party suppliers. Although VacationParties.com members may   rate and review particular properties based on their own experiences,   VacationParties.com does not endorse or recommend the products or services of   any third-party suppliers. You agree that VacationParties.com is not responsible   for the accuracy or completeness of information it obtains from   third-party suppliers and displays on its sites or apps.</p>\r\n<p>If you book a reservation with a third-party supplier, you agree to   review and be bound by the supplier&rsquo;s terms and conditions of purchase   and site use (the &ldquo;Terms of Use&rdquo;), Privacy Policy, and any other rules   or policies related to the supplier&rsquo;s site or property. Your   interactions with third-party suppliers are at your own risk.   VacationParties.com will have no liability with respect to the acts, omissions,   errors, representations, warranties, breaches or negligence of any   third-party suppliers or for any personal injuries, death, property   damage, or other damages or expenses resulting from your interactions   with third-party suppliers.</p>\r\n<p>This Website may link you to supplier sites or other websites that   VacationParties.com does not operate or control. For further information, please   refer to the &ldquo;Links to Third-Party Sites&rdquo; section below.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Booking Vacation Rentals with Third-Party Suppliers Listed on Affiliate Sites.</strong> VacationParties.com and some of its affiliates act as marketplaces to allow   travelers to enter into vacation rental agreements or rental   transactions with property owners and managers (each, an &ldquo;Advertiser&rdquo;).   As a user, you must be responsible for your use of this Website, our   affiliate sites, and any transaction involving vacation rentals   facilitated by the Booking Systems-++and/or listed on affiliate sites. We do   not own, manage, or contract for any vacation rental property listed on   this Website or our affiliate sites.</p>\r\n<p>Because neither VacationParties.com nor its affiliates are parties to rental   transactions between travelers and Advertisers, any dispute or conflict   involving an actual or potential transaction bet