(23, 0, 'Caliente Caribe | Clothing Optional | Dominican Republic | Resort', '', '<strong>Caliente Caribe, Only Clothing Optional ResortÃ¢â‚¬Â¨ In The Dominican Republic</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nCaliente Caribe is as laid-back or high-energy as you wish, and offers beautiful appointments featuring ocean views and direct access to its own private nude beach.&nbsp; Because the entire resort is clothing optional, you can feel as free as you want, anywhere, any time.<br />\r\nLocated near Puerto Plata, Dominican Republic, Caliente Caribe is an oasis of luxury in an unspoiled environment, where coconut palms sway by day and Club Caribe rocks by night - giving you a holiday getaway you&#39;ll not soon forget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<strong>Caliente Caribe in Abreu Dominican Republic</strong><br />\r\nIn a place where tropical forests and streams spill over mountainsides and into an aquamarine sea, Caliente Caribe sets a clothing optional standard no other Caribbean vacation resort can match.<br />\r\nCaliente Caribe is hugged by a wide expanse of sapphire Caribbean water. Located in one of the Caribbean&rsquo;s most applauded vacation spots, arriving at Caliente Caribe is like stepping into a postcard. And because it&rsquo;s all-inclusive, one price leads to one unbelievable vacation.', '<p><strong>Luxury Inclusive Caliente Caribe</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Caliente Caribe is All-Inclusive so your room rate includes everything!</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Romantic gourmet dining</li>\r\n	<li>Unlimited premium cocktails</li>\r\n	<li>Afternoon and late night snacks</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel tax</li>\r\n	<li>Beach and water activities</li>\r\n	<li>Nightclub &amp; Karaoke</li>\r\n	<li>Fitness facilities</li>\r\n	<li>Rates include round trip ground transfer on reservations 6 nights and over to Caliente Caribe from Puerto Plata and Santo Domingo airports.</li>\r\n	<li>Transfers are not included for special incentive rates, some groups, VacationClub Members, Exotic Members, RCI bookings, owners and all non-revenue trips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Gourmet Dining at Caribe</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast and dinner are served in the main restaurant, located at the top of a small picturesque sea cliff, features al fresco (open air) dining at it&rsquo;s romantic best! The views are simply incredible and the food exquisite. Choose to dine with friends or enjoy a table for two.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All meal choices vary and there is always something new to enjoy. However, if you have a special request or any restrictions, please contact Patricia Gorden our General Manager at the resort at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:pgorden@calienteresorts.com">pgorden@calienteresorts.com</a>she will do her best to have the kitchen accommodate you. Lunch and snacks are served at the ocean level Tiki Bar just 15 meters from the beach.&nbsp;All meals are full service except our Friday Night Luau Pig Roast Buffet at the Tiki with a bonfire on the beach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unlimited Premium Beverages</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From water and colas to top-shelf liquors, wines and tropical delights... everything is included in unlimited quantities! Our current well is composed of local offerings as well as favorites you know and love, including Rum&rsquo;s like: Brugal Dorado (dark), Brugal Blanco, Brugal 151, Marcoiris Agua Coco, Bacardi Blanco and Barcelo Anejo. Gin&rsquo;s like: Bermudez and Tangueray.&nbsp; Vodka&rsquo;s like: Red Russian and Absolut.&nbsp; Whiskey&rsquo;s like: Jim Beam, Jack Daniels, Canadian Club and Dewars.&nbsp; Jose Cuervo Tequila.&nbsp; Sambuca.&nbsp; Cointreau.&nbsp; Baileys Irish Cream, Kahlua, Amaretto, Cr&egrave;me de Mente.&nbsp; Campari. And last but not least, Brandi&rsquo;s like: Napoleon and Fortier.&nbsp; Our local beer available to us as part of the all-inclusive is El&#39; Presedente and Bohemian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have a favorite brand that we do not have on hand and is available locally, we will be more than happy to acquire it for you at the current local price.&nbsp; This purchase will be charged to your room.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also purchase a bottle personally for your room at the airport duty free.&nbsp; Remember to keep in mind you are in another country and some liquors are not available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>DAILY ACTIVITIES</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="7" class="mceItemTable" style="border:1px dashed rgb(187, 187, 187); cursor:default; font-family:verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top"><em><strong>Monday:</strong></em></td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">Shuffle Board</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top"><em><strong>Tuesday:</strong></em></td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">Testicle Toss</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top"><em><strong>Wednesday:</strong></em></td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">Bocce Ball</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top"><em><strong>Thursday:</strong></em></td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">Testicle Toss</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top"><em><strong>Friday:</strong></em></td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">Darts</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top"><em><strong>Saturday:</strong></em></td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">Rock Painting</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top"><em><strong>Sunday:</strong></em></td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">Bocce Ball</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>AFTERNOON GAMES</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="7" class="mceItemTable" style="border:1px dashed rgb(187, 187, 187); cursor:default; font-family:verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td s